---
description: Kubebuilder marker & CEL policy for this repo. Apply when editing kubebuilder validation markers under api/**.
globs: api/**/*.go
alwaysApply: false
---

- Prefer standard markers (`Enum`, `MinLength`, `Minimum`, `MinItems`, `Required`) when they suffice.
- `+kubebuilder:validation:XValidation` (CEL → `x-kubernetes-validations`) is ALLOWED and used for
  invariants standard markers can't express — cross-field / transition rules (immutability on
  `api/storage`; the `ManifestCaptureRequest` non-empty-`targets` rule on `api/v1alpha1`). Reach for CEL
  only when a standard marker cannot express the constraint.
- **CEL needs an integration test (MUST):** CEL is enforced by the kube-apiserver; a fake-client unit
  test bypasses it and proves nothing. Any added/changed CEL rule requires an envtest asserting
  apiserver reject-on-violation + accept-on-valid — see `cel-requires-integration-test`.
- After any marker change: `bash hack/generate_code.sh` (from repo root) and commit the regenerated CRDs.
